			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Rixsar wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">3 ticks of health doesnt do much when you getting ripped by a mob</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
I have to disagree there.  Although 3 ticks won't save you while being pounded on, the overall effect <span style="font-weight: bold">stacks</span> with others and can make a lot of difference in healing back up after a fight, or counteracting a DoT. 
<br />

<br />
1.  XPG = Increase Hitpoints by 8 per tick
<br />
2.  My Phylactery clicky buff = 2 per tick
<br />
3.  My Regen 3 AA = 3 per tick
<br />
4.  My gear has added 5 per tick 
<br />

<br />
Now that is an added 18 per tick HP.  For a class that cannot heal itself at all, regen is the only way to gain HP back while soloing.   And considering I MOD ROD constantly, I need all the regen I can get.
<br />

<br />
I can take a few hits during a fight, and afterwards sit down and heal back up again quickly enough (around 40hp/tick sitting).  Also, it can save me from a DoT spell landing on me by counteracting some of the HP loss with regen gains.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4796" target="_blank" class="postlink"><span style="font-weight: bold"><span style="color: #FF0000"><span style="font-size: 15px; line-height: normal">Lord Zacatac Soulwanderer</a></span></span></span>
